doc.after: Ovarian cancer usually has a relatively poor prognosis It is disproportionately deadly because it lacks any clear early detection or screening test meaning most cases are not diagnosed until they have reached advanced stages 51 However in some cases ovarian cancer recurrences are chronically treatable 10
